title: Part A
stimulusHtml:
2 points maximum

1 point for stating that methane can be burned and 1 point for describing how this generates electricity:

  • By producing steam to turn a turbine (to rotate coils in a magnetic field), OR

  • Through use in internal combustion engine to turn a turbine (to rotate coils in a magnetic

    field).

title: Part C
stimulusHtml:
5 points maximum

  • 2 points maximum


    1 point is earned for the correct setup and 1 point for the correct answer. (Units are not required, but the student must show calculations in order to receive the answer point.)


    500  cows  × 3.0  kWh cow-day × 365  days year = 547 , 500  kWh/year


    OR
     

    1500 kWh day × 365  days year = 547 , 500  kWh/year

  • 2 points maximum


    1 point is earned for the correct setup and 1 point for the correct answer. (Units are not required, but the student must show calculations in order to receive the answer point.) Incorrect answers transferred from (c)(i) can still earn full credit if used correctly.

    547, 500 kWh x $0.10 = $54,750 ($55,000)

    OR

    800,000 kWh - 547,5000 kWh = 252,500 kWh needed from a utility.





     

    800,000 x $0.10 = $80,000

    252,500 x $0.10 = $25,250

    $80,000 - $25,250 - $54, 750 or $55,000 saved.

  • 1 point maximum

    1 point is earned for the correct setup AND correct answer. (Units are not required, but the student must show calculations in order to receive the point). Incorrect answers transferred from (c)(ii) can still earn full credit if used correctly.

    $400,000/$55,000 = 7.2 years (or 7 years)
